HEADWORD: Acrocarpous
<hw>Ac`ro*car"pous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
extreme, highest + <?/ fruit.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Having a terminal fructification; having the fruit at the end of
the stalk.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Having the fruit stalks at the end of
a leafy stem, as in certain mosses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

